<p>I'd like to set a MultiDataTrigger for a TextBox as shown in the code below.</p>  <p>If IsNormal property, which I defined in the code-behind, is false and the TextBox is in the 2nd row of a Grid, IsEnabled of it should be false.</p>  <p>However, the Condition regarding the Grid.Row does not work properly.</p>  <p>Could you tell me how it is possible to use a Grid.Row property as a binding path in this case?</p>  <pre><code>&lt;Style TargetType="TextBox"&gt;     &lt;Style.Triggers&gt;         &lt;MultiDataTrigger&gt;             &lt;MultiDataTrigger.Conditions&gt;                 &lt;Condition Binding="{Binding RelativeSource={RelativeSource FindAncestor, AncestorType=UserControl}, Path=IsNormal}"                             Value="False"/&gt;                 &lt;Condition Binding="{Binding RelativeSource={RelativeSource Self}, Path=Grid.Row}"                            Value="2"/&gt;             &lt;/MultiDataTrigger.Conditions&gt;             &lt;Setter Property="IsEnabled" Value="False"/&gt;         &lt;/MultiDataTrigger&gt;     &lt;/Style.Triggers&gt; &lt;/Style&gt; </code></pre>